                        <summary>The word ἐκχώρηϲιϲ indicates that the document is a cession of property, perhaps of grainland. Also a house might have been involved.</summary>
                        <msItemStruct>
                            <note type="general">The text proper must have had an estimated 120–50 lines, followed by subscriptions of some 15 lines. There were ample top (10–30 cm) and bottom margins at least (20 cm). The scribe used a right margin of 2–4 cm, and he tended to ﬁll the line-ends by extending the last letter with a horizontal stroke. The subscriptions had a narrower margin of just 0.5–1 cm. Written in capital letters.</note>
